Float formatting:

Syntax:
{value:width.precision f}"

precision defines the number of decimal places till
we want our results and make it to round number till that point.

width: how long you want to result to be.


result = 100/777
print('the result {r:1.2}".format(r=result))
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
f ---->
fstring
f'  -------------> formatting string literals.
name="shivam"
print(f'"this is my name{name})" 
